### Perform Multiple $pull Operations with `bulkWrite`

Source: https://github.com/mongodb/docs/blob/main/content/manual/manual/source/reference/operator/update/pull.txt

Demonstrates using `db.collection.bulkWrite()` to insert a document and then perform two `$pull` operations, removing elements greater than or equal to 6 and less than or equal to 3 from the `votes` array.

```javascript
try {
      db.profilesBulkWrite.bulkWrite( [
         {
            insertOne: {
               ""document"": { _id: 1, votes: [ 3, 5, 6, 7, 7, 8 ] }
            }
         },
         {
            updateOne: {
               ""filter"": { _id: 1 }, 
               ""update"": { $pull: { votes: { $gte: 6 } } }
            }
         },
         {
            updateOne: {
               ""filter"": {_id: 1}, 
               ""update"": { $pull: { votes: { $lte: 3 } } }
            }
         }
      ] );
   } catch (e) {
      print(e);
   }
```

