### Update Array Elements with Filtered Positional Operator (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/mongodb/docs/blob/main/content/manual/manual/source/reference/method/db.collection.findAndModify.txt

Updates elements in the 'grades' array that are greater than or equal to 100, using arrayFilters and the filtered positional operator.

```javascript
db.students.findAndModify({
      query: { grades: { $gte: 100 } },
      update: { $set: { ""grades.$[element]"" : 100 } },
      arrayFilters: [ { ""element"": { $gte: 100 } } ]
   })
```

